WAHTARI LICENCE AGREEMENT

IMPORTANT - read carefully

PLEASE READ THIS AGREEMENT CAREFULLY BEFORE DOWNLOADING OR USING THE SOFTWARE. 
By downloading or using the Software, YOU AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THE CONTENTS OF THIS AGREEMENT.
If YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THE CONTENTS OF THIS AGREEMENT, DO NOT DOWNLOAD SOFTWARE FROM THIS WEBSITE.
THIS LICENSE AGREEMENT ("AGREEMENT") IS A LEGAL SETTLEMENT BETWEEN WAHTARI GmbH ("Wahtari") and the users of the software products provided ("SOFTWARE"). 

1. THIRD PARTY SOFTWARE. Not withstanding this Agreement, all or a portion of the SOFTWARE that is not Wahtari-owned software provided under an open source license by a third party ("Third Party Software") will be made available to you pursuant to the terms and conditions of the license agreement underlying the Third Party Software. 
The use of such Third Party Software is entirely subject to the terms of this Licence. You can find the terms under "LICENSE-deps". 
Wahtari software contains some open source software source code that can be used and modified by anyone, provided that you in turn make it available to everyone else with the same licence agreement.

2. GRANT OF LICENSE. You are granted a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable right to use the Wahtari SOFTWARE upon your acceptance of and compliance with all of the terms and conditions of this Agreement.

3. PERMITTED software use. You may install and use the SOFTWARE indefinitely. The SOFTWARE may only be used to operate Wahtari products.

4. TRANSFER. Except as expressly permitted in this Section 4, you may not rent, lease, sublicense or loan the SOFTWARE or any portion thereof. You may transfer the SOFTWARE, in whole or in part (individual files, e.g. DLLs, etc.), to another entity or person, provided that the transferee accepts the terms of this AGREEMENT.

5.1 RESTRICTIONS. You may copy or use the SOFTWARE only as provided in this Agreement. You may not remove any proprietary notices or labels on the SOFTWARE; all copies made in compliance with this Agreement must include all copyright and other proprietary notices that exist on and in the SOFTWARE.

5.2 RESTRICTION ON REVERSE ENGINEERING. Except as provided in this Agreement, you may not modify, adapt, reverse engineer, decompile or dissemble the SOFTWARE or otherwise attempt to discover the source code or algorithms contained in the SOFTWARE or create derivative works based on the SOFTWARE.

6. PROPRIETARY RIGHTS. All intellectual property rights in the SOFTWARE are owned by Wahtari or its suppliers and are protected by copyright laws and international copyright treaties. Product identification, copyright notices or proprietary restrictions may not be removed from the SOFTWARE.


7.1 LIABILITY (GERMANY). 

a) Wahtari shall be liable without limitation for intent and gross negligence.

b) Wahtari is liable for ordinary negligence - except in the case of injury to life, body or health - only if material contractual obligations (cardinal obligations) are breached. Liability shall be limited to the foreseeable damage typical for the contract.

c) Liability for indirect and unforeseeable damage, loss of production and use, loss of profit, loss of savings and financial loss due to claims by third parties is excluded in the case of simple negligence, except in the case of injury to life, limb or health.

d) Any further liability other than that stipulated in this contract is excluded, irrespective of the legal nature of the asserted claim. The foregoing limitations or exclusions of liability shall not, however, apply to any strict liability prescribed by law (e.g. under the Product Liability Act) or to liability under a strict warranty.

e) Insofar as liability is excluded or limited pursuant to clauses b and c, this shall also apply to the personal liability of Wahtari's employees, workers, representatives, bodies and vicarious agents.

f) Some states/jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion or limitation of incidental or consequential damages, so the above limitation or exclusion may not apply to you.

7.2 LIABILITY (INTERNATIONAL). TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, WAHTARI AND ITS SUPPLIERS PROVIDE THE SOFTWARE "AS IS" AND WITH ALL FAULTS and hereby also excludes for all other jurisdictions any and all claims for arbitration to the extent permitted by the respective laws.
In particular, Wahtari HEREBY DISCLAIMS ALL OTHER WARRANTIES AND CONDITIONS, EITHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, WARRANTIES OF TITLE AND NON-INFRINGEMENT, ANY IMPLIED WARRANTIES, DUTIES OR CONDITIONS OF MERCHANTABILITY, OF FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND OF LACK OF VIRUSES ALL WITH REGARD TO THE SOFTWARE.


8. APPLICABLE LAW AND JURISDICTION. This Agreement is made and construed in accordance with German law. The Amtsgericht (local court) of Munich shall have jurisdiction over any dispute between the parties arising out of this Agreement. The failure of either party to enforce any provision of this Agreement shall not be deemed a waiver of any future right to enforce that or any other provision.

9. GENERAL. This Agreement is the complete and exclusive statement of the agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior agreements and communications with respect to the subject matter hereof. This Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties and their respective successors and assigns and may be modified only by an instrument signed by both parties. If any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid, the offending clause shall be modified so as to be enforceable and shall be fully enforced as modified. In such event, the remainder of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect.



